{
  "stem": "5810.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I saw Germans shoot Jews all over the place in-- in daylight.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They weren't hiding.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were in uniform.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It wasn't a secret.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These things were happening.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So why did this happen?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I questioned that for a lot of years later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But at that time, I knew only one thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't connect it with that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the store and the textile factory that we had was all of a sudden instead of producing sweaters for people, for-- for retail market-- we were just producing hats.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember that very distinctly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I also remember that those hats were never sold in the store, but every once in a while there was a truck with Germans that came by and picked up these cartons full of hats.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I don't believe I asked then what that was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It wasn't-- it wasn't clear to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was just too young to understand any of this connection.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I later on [SIGHS] asked many questions after the war, and some during the war, and found out that in those days a lot of Jews did what they had to do to survive another day, and to protect their family.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I came to find out-- and this I believe in very, very strongly today, so I can live with that-- that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] deals were made.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That the Germans used whatever skills they could get out of the Jews at that time, whether they were diamond cutters, or whether they were manufacturers or whatever.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They used their skills for their purposes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I came to understand that because he was in textile, and he understood all about sewing and doing and manufacturing clothing, that these hats were necessary.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
